tags: [[Hidden Settings]]
title: Resilient Rendering (Example)
caption: Resilient Render (example)
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

This example shows [[Hidden Setting: Resilient Render]] in action — how a faulty widget degrades //on a gradient// rather than crashing the whole view.

!! The gradient

TiddlyWiki already handles some failures gracefully. A working widget renders; an //unknown// widget degrades to a placeholder; and — with Resilient Render enabled — a widget that actually //throws// degrades to an error span instead of aborting the tiddler. The tiddler keeps rendering throughout:

<<wikitext-example-without-html """A working widget: <$text text="I render fine"/>

An unknown widget (degraded natively by TiddlyWiki): <$totally-made-up-widget/>""">>

The third rung — a widget that //throws// — can't be shown statically (with the setting off it would, correctly, fail the build). Try it live instead.

!! Try it live (click-to-edit)

First enable the setting:

<$checkbox tiddler="$:/config/ResilientRender" field="text" checked="yes" unchecked="no" default="no"> Contain render errors (`$:/config/ResilientRender`)</$checkbox>

Now edit the text below. Type a deliberately-failing widget — `<$error-demo fail="render"/>` — alongside normal content, and watch the preview update on every keystroke: the failing widget becomes a `tc-error` span while everything around it keeps rendering. Turn the setting off and the same input aborts the preview instead (fail-loud).

<$edit-text tiddler="$:/temp/resilient-demo" tag="textarea" class="tc-edit-texteditor" placeholder="Type wikitext here, e.g. before <$error-demo fail render/> after"/>

Preview:

<div class="tc-resilient-demo-preview" style="border:1px solid #ccc; padding:0.5em;">
<$transclude tiddler="$:/temp/resilient-demo" mode="block"/>
</div>

The same boundary protects //refresh//, not just first render: with the setting on, a widget that throws on a later update (here, `<$error-demo fail="refresh"/>`) is contained the moment it fails, so a live, click-to-edit interface keeps working instead of going blank.
